{
  "texts": [
    "Flow-based models' tractable likelihoods make them useful for applications such as anomaly identification and uncertainty quantification.",
    "Furthermore, in circumstances requiring stable training and convergence, particularly in large-scale generating tasks, diffusion models outperform GANs by resolving training stability difficulties.As a result, the choice between various generative models is determined by the task's unique criteria, such as the necessity for interpretable latent spaces, explicit density estimates, or improved training stability.",
    "Understanding the benefits and limits of each model type is critical for making educated decisions based on the data's properties and the generating task's aims.",
    "Review studies of popular GAN models based on architecture and loss optimizationSeveral GAN variants are developed as enhancements of the base GAN model to eliminate its limitations of instability and complexities at the time of model training.",
    "The variants developed and are evaluated many times to identify the prime potentialities and scope of further improvements."
  ]
}